### Project: faultline (previous session)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/faultline
**Status:** All 8 tasks (301-308) completed and pushed.

Drop-in replacement for `github.com/pkg/errors` (Go library).

**Key implementation details:**
- Module: `github.com/agentine/faultline`, Go 1.21+, zero dependencies
- `stack.go`: stack capture via `runtime.Callers(3, pcs)`, `Frame`/`StackTrace` types with lazy resolution
- `errors.go`: `fundamental` struct (msg + stack), `New`/`Errorf`
- `wrap.go`: Three wrapper types:
  - `withStack` (cause + stack, no message)
  - `withMessage` (cause + message, no stack)
  - `withCause` (cause + message + stack) — result of `Wrap`/`Wrapf`
  - All implement both `Cause()` and `Unwrap()` — the critical fix for errors.Is/errors.As compatibility
- `format.go`: Package doc only; Format() methods live on each type
- `Cause()` function walks both Cause() and Unwrap() chains to root
- %+v output matches pkg/errors format exactly

**Tests:** 30+ tests across 7 test files, all passing with `-race`. Includes:
- Unit tests (errors, wrap, stack, format)
- Compatibility tests (errors.Is/errors.As through all wrapper types)
- Benchmarks (New, Errorf, Wrap, Wrapf, WithStack, WithMessage, Cause, Format)
- Godoc examples

**CI:** GitHub Actions with Go 1.21/1.22/1.23/stable matrix, golangci-lint, staticcheck

**Docs:** README.md (badge, API ref, migration guide, benchmarks), CHANGELOG.md (v0.1.0)

