### Project: isochron (this session — 21 tasks)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/isochron
**Status:** All 21 tasks completed and pushed.

Pure-Python ISO 8601 date/time/duration/interval parsing and formatting library — drop-in isodate replacement.

**Key implementation details:**
- Python >=3.10, BSD-3-Clause, hatchling build
- Modules: _parse_date, _parse_time, _parse_datetime, _parse_duration, _parse_interval, _parse_tz, _format, _strftime, _duration, _tz, _errors, _compat
- Duration: frozen dataclass with years/months/days/seconds/microseconds, arithmetic ops, to_timedelta()
- Compat shim (_compat.py, compat/__init__.py) maps all isodate public names
- Fixes for isodate issues: #85 (T24:00:00), #87 (second rounding), #89 (UTC→Z), #90 (second out-of-range), #95 (total_seconds ValueError for non-fixed), #96/#97 (duration parsing)

**Tests:** 128 tests (test_phase1: 79, test_phase2: 39, test_compat: 10) — all passing
**CI:** Python 3.10-3.13, ubuntu+macos matrix, pytest + mypy
**Docs:** README.md, CHANGELOG.md, benchmarks/

**Fixes during implementation:**
- Duration __add__ overload ordering: datetime overload before date (datetime is date subclass)
- Unused Union import removed
- `gh repo create` for initial push

